Here’s a tidy, ready‑to‑drop CSS snippet that defines the color tokens, typography, and example classes for each tone section.  
It’s lightweight and accessible for both light and dark modes.  

```css
/* ---------- Root Tokens ---------- */
:root {
  /* Brand neutrals */
  --text-base-light: #1C1C1C;
  --text-base-dark:  #F4F4F4;
  --divider-light:   #CCCCCC;
  --divider-dark:    #444444;

  /* Tone colors */
  --tone-safety-light:   #006E90;   /* deep teal */
  --tone-safety-dark:    #80C4D8;
  --tone-grounding-light:#145A32;   /* forest green */
  --tone-grounding-dark: #7FBF80;
  --tone-agency-light:   #C47F00;   /* warm amber */
  --tone-agency-dark:    #FFD27F;

  /* Accent gradient for footer cue */
  --accent-gradient: linear-gradient(to right,
    #006E90, #145A32, #C47F00);
}

/* ---------- Base Typography ---------- */
body {
  font-family: "Noto Sans", "Open Sans", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
  font-size: 16px;
  line-height: 1.5;
  color: var(--text-base-light);
  background: #fff;
}

[data-theme="dark"] body {
  color: var(--text-base-dark);
  background: #111;
}

/* ---------- Headings / Mantras ---------- */
h1, h2, h3 {
  font-family: "Source Sans Pro", "IBM Plex Sans", sans-serif;
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: 0.5px;
}

/* ---------- Tone Blocks ---------- */
.tone-safety {
  border-left: 6px solid var(--tone-safety-light);
  padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
}

.tone-grounding {
  border-left: 6px solid var(--tone-grounding-light);
  padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
}

.tone-agency {
  border-left: 6px solid var(--tone-agency-light);
  padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
}

/* Adjust colors in dark theme */
[data-theme="dark"] .tone-safety {
  border-color: var(--tone-safety-dark);
}
[data-theme="dark"] .tone-grounding {
  border-color: var(--tone-grounding-dark);
}
[data-theme="dark"] .tone-agency {
  border-color: var(--tone-agency-dark);
}

/* ---------- Footer Cue ---------- */
.footer-flow {
  height: 6px;
  width: 100%;
  background: var(--accent-gradient);
  border-radius: 2px;
  margin-top: 1rem;
}
```

**Usage Example**
```html
<div class="tone-safety">
  <h3>Safety Tone — "Connect first."</h3>
  <p>Help them feel seen & safe before reasoning.</p>
</div>

<div class="tone-grounding">
  <h3>Grounding Tone — "Slow and steady."</h3>
  <p>Ease overload; focus on one small piece at a time.</p>
</div>

<div class="tone-agency">
  <h3>Agency Tone — "Forward with respect."</h3>
  <p>Affirm effort and plan a small next step.</p>
</div>

<div class="footer-flow"></div>
```

This gives a designer or moderator dashboard a clean, high‑contrast appearance aligned with the **Connect → Regulate → Empower** framework.

